Business Brief -- Masco Industries Inc.:
   Two Year-End Transactions
   Bring In About $150 Million
In the second transaction, Masco garnered $120 million
from distributions and loan repayments by Masco Capital Corp.
and from the 50% interest in Masco Capital that Masco
Industries sold to the other Masco Capital stockholder, Masco
Corp.
   Although Masco Industries will realize a gain on the first
redemption, it said it expects to post roughly break-even
earnings for the fourth quarter of 1991. The company makes
custom-engineered and other commercial and specialty
industrial products.